psalm.text:
[[Ps 27,1]]The LORD is my light and my salvation; 
whom should I fear? 
The LORD is my life's refuge; 
of whom should I be afraid?

[[Ps 27,3]]Though an army encamp against me, 
my heart will not fear; 
Though war be waged upon me, 
even then will I trust.

[[Ps 27,5]]For he will hide me in his abode 
in the day of trouble; 
He will conceal me in the shelter of his tent, 
he will set me high upon a rock.

[[Ps 27,8b]]Your presence, O LORD, I seek.
[[Ps 27,9a]]Hide not your face from me;
[[Ps 27,9b]]do not in anger repel your servant.
[[Ps 27,9c]]You are my helper: cast me not off.
